    {
      "id": "PopularPost82841",
      "post_content": "@Dragonlord: Your reasoning is flawed. Most of the cards you compare this to are multi-colored. [Wrench Mind](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Wrench Mind) is only slightly better and has a double black mana cost along with a possible drawback. [Delerium Skeins](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delerium Skeins) is only better if you're doing Madness or Hellbent. [Hymn to Tourach](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hymn to Tourach) is universally agreed to be overpowered, which is why they've never printed anything close to it in the last 10 years, and probably never will. And don't get me started on Blightning...  \nThis is an extremely balanced card. In older decks it can still be played on the first turn with a Dark Ritual, and it fits into any multicolor deck using black.",
      "posted_by": "achilleselbow",
