    {
      "id": "PopularPost76151",
      "post_content": "If you're wanting a B discard, splash in the red, give them some draw with [Sign in Blood](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sign in Blood), [Howling Mine](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Howling Mine), or [Font of Mythos](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Font of Mythos), then toss in your [Underworld Dreams](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Underworld Dreams) since you're pumping their hand up with some [Megrim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Megrim) to trim. Then use your [Blightning](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blightning) to nail them for 7 with the megrim, making sure they'll have a hand. Sure, there is definitely room for this card in discard, but if you're wanting to use Megrim to burn them as they discard, [Burning Inquiry](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Burning Inquiry) is infinitely better, it ensures they will have cards in hand, only costs 1 mana, and discards an extra. It will do 2 more damage, and only 1 less than Blightning.  \n  \nIf anyone likes the deck idea, [Chandra Ablaze](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chandra Ablaze) and [Liliana Vess](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Liliana Vess) to taste.  \n  \nAnd for everyone crying about Blightning being undercosted, it doesn't tag on a [lightning bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=lightning bolt). Th... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "OpenSeasonNoobs",
